  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375 degrees.",
    "Roll out the empanada dough to a thickness of 1/8 inch.",
    "Cut out circles of dough using a cookie cutter or the rim of a glass.",
    "Place a tablespoon of taleggio cheese in the center of each dough circle.",
    "Add a sprinkle of chopped onion, garlic, and jalapeno pepper on top of the cheese.",
    "Fold the dough in half and press the edges together to seal the empanada.",
    "Use a fork to crimp the edges and create a decorative border.",
    "Place the empanadas in a ramekin and brush the tops with olive oil.",
    "Bake the empanadas for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.",
    "Serve the empanadas hot and enjoy."
  ],
